{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Double Government UK civil space spending from its current level by 2030",
        "additional_details": "We believe space investment brings strong economic returns, supports innovation & skills, strengthens national capability, & helps the UK secure industrial, scientific, & inspirational benefits. The UK Space Agency says every \u00a31 invested in space generates over \u00a37 for the UK economy. We feel increased space investment would make the UK\u2019s 2022 National Space Strategy & 2024 Space Industrial Plan viable & achievable. A 2025 House of Lords report warns the UK must act now to lead in the growing space economy.",
        "background": "Support the UK to join other developed nations and expand its role in international space exploration, science, and utilisation, thus properly supporting growth, security, and highly-skilled jobs. The UK is a major economy, but has fallen behind comparable countries in government space investment.",
